## PHASE 4 — Geometry Normalization (FIX 1)
- [ ] Create `processing/geometry.py`
- [ ] Implement:
  - [ ] `distance(p1, p2)`
  - [ ] `inter_ocular_distance(landmarks)`
  - [ ] `normalized_distance(p1, p2, iod)`
- [ ] Use `IOD = distance(33, 263)`
- [ ] Apply to all distance-based features
- [ ] Formula check: `normalized = distance(p1, p2) / IOD`

## PHASE 5 — Head Pose Stabilization (FIX 2)
- [ ] Create `processing/head_pose.py`
- [ ] Implement:
  - [ ] `estimate_head_pose()`
  - [ ] `reject_unstable_frames()`
  - [ ] `align_landmarks()`
- [ ] Compute yaw, pitch, roll using `cv2.solvePnP()`
- [ ] Use anchor points:
  - [ ] `1` (nose)
  - [ ] `33` (left eye)
  - [ ] `263` (right eye)
  - [ ] `152` (chin)
- [ ] Frame rejection rules:
  - [ ] `|yaw| > 35°`
  - [ ] `|pitch| > 25°`
- [ ] If unstable, skip feature update

## PHASE 6 — Frame Buffer
- [ ] Create `core/frame_buffer.py`
- [ ] Use `buffer = deque(maxlen=150)`
- [ ] Store per frame:
  - [ ] `timestamp`
  - [ ] `landmarks`
  - [ ] `head_pose`
  - [ ] `features`
- [ ] Verify: 150 frames ≈ 10 seconds at 15 FPS

## PHASE 7 — Feature Base Class
- [ ] Create `features/base_feature.py`
- [ ] Add base class:

```python
class BaseFeature:
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name
        self.history = []

    def compute(self, landmarks, frame_buffer, timestamp):
        raise NotImplementedError

    def update_history(self, value):
        self.history.append(value)
```

- [ ] Ensure all features inherit from this class

