## PHASE 9 — Feature Registry
- [ ] Create `core/feature_registry.py`
- [ ] Register all 34 feature classes
- [ ] Structure:

```python
FEATURE_REGISTRY = [
    AU12Mean(),
    AU12Variance(),
    BlinkRate(),
    MeanHeadVelocity(),
    # ... all remaining features
]
```

- [ ] Pipeline execution pattern:

```python
for feature in FEATURE_REGISTRY:
    value = feature.compute(landmarks, frame_buffer, timestamp)
```

## PHASE 10 — EMA Smoothing (FIX 3)
- [ ] Create `processing/ema_smoothing.py`
- [ ] Implement EMA:

```text
EMA_t = αx_t + (1 − α)EMA_(t−1)
```

- [ ] Default `α = 0.3`
- [ ] Apply after raw feature computation

## PHASE 11 — Baseline System
- [ ] Collect baseline for 10 seconds
- [ ] Compute per feature:
  - [ ] mean (`μ`)
  - [ ] standard deviation (`σ`)

## PHASE 12 — Feature Normalization
- [ ] Apply:

```text
z = (value − μ) / σ
scaled = 1 / (1 + e^(−z))
```

- [ ] Output range check: `0 to 1`

## PHASE 13 — CSV Logging
- [ ] Create `output/csv_logger.py`
- [ ] Log timestamp + 34 scaled features + raw features values as well and the naming format for the csv must be HH(hour)_MM(month)_DD(date)_MM(month).csv
- [ ] Example header:

```text
timestamp,S_AU12Mean,S_BlinkRate,S_EyeContactRatio,...
```

- [ ] Header length check: 35 columns (1 timestamp + 34 features)

## PHASE 14 — Pipeline Runner
- [ ] Create `run_pipeline.py`
- [ ] Main loop order:
  - [ ] capture frame
  - [ ] detect landmarks
  - [ ] extract subset
  - [ ] normalize geometry
  - [ ] estimate head pose
  - [ ] add to frame buffer
  - [ ] compute features
  - [ ] apply EMA
  - [ ] normalize
  - [ ] log CSV

